<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="IMPORTANT_NOTE_This_document_is"></a> IMPORTANT NOTE: This document is no longer being used as the means to collect requirements/feature requests for the OIM project. Instead we're using our <a href="http://code.google.com/p/osggoc/issues/list" target="_top">bug-report/feature-request tool here</a>. </span></h2>
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Feature_Additions_Immediate"></a> Feature Additions Immediate </span></h2>
<p /> <ul>
<li> Restricted, and Private access to registration information view. <ul>
<li> 
</li> <li> Authorized views of OIM data for registered users:  <ul>
<li> Contacts for various entities 
</li></ul> 
</li> <li> Add Area to create CSV files of OIM data (later) 
</li></ul> 
</li></ul> 
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Bug_fixes_Errors_ASAP_Timeframe"></a> Bug fixes/Errors - ASAP Timeframe -- in order of decreasing priority. </span></h2> <ul>
<li> Add check so that a service must be selected when setting a maintenance. 
</li></ul> 
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Immediate_ASAP_Timeframe_in_orde"></a> Immediate - ASAP Timeframe -- in order of decreasing priority. </span></h2> <ul>
<li> Add authentication access ranges as a function. Use config file so we can easily add new authentication ranges if need be. Arvind to expand upon this. 
</li> <li> Validation for maintenance form that ensures someone cannot setup two overlapping maintenance records for the same resource-service mapping 
</li> <li> Bug in edit_resource form - If "Default/fake" facility and site chosen at resource_add time, then attempts to edit that resource, produce a foreign key constraint -- I can replicate the error if you need me to -agopu mid 2008-06, 2008-07-11 
</li></ul> 
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Short_term_Timeframe"></a> Short term Timeframe </span></h2>
<p /> <ul>
<li> Edit_AddedContact: For added contacts, can you slip in a "None - no DN associated with this user yet, contact GOC if you'd like this user to become active on OIM" type message? next to the Certificate DN: <blank> row 
</li> <li> Web form so that any registered OIM user can send email to any list. (osggeneral, osg-sites, etc) 
</li> <li> Add SC contact information (read-only) on resource and SC registration views. 
</li> <li> Edit_Person: Display all updated user info once user is updated 
</li> <li> resource/resource.php: Does not show anything in site if the "Default site" is chosen .. it'd be nice if you showed some off-colored text that said "appropriate facility and site" are not assigned to this resource -- contact GOC, blah blah.. 
</li> <li> <a href="/bin/view/Operations/UpdateEmailTemplates" class="twikiLink">Update Email Templates</a> 
</li> <li> Add signing to all OIM correspondence.  <ul>
<li> add an email form so GOC can send email to any OIM user. 
</li></ul> 
</li> <li> Edit all persons (admin) interface should show DN of person in each row -- ideally, the page would show name, email, phone, DN in some sort of tabular format. 
</li></ul> 
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Medium_term_Timeframe"></a> Medium term Timeframe </span></h2>
<p /> <ul>
<li> ADMIN-Resource -- Allows me to activate a resource even though:  <ul>
<li> it does not have a proper facility/site associated with it. 
</li> <li> it does not have the required contacts in it yet. 
</li></ul> 
</li> <li> Is the primary, secondary, etc contacts automatically generated? I.e if a particular contact has more than 2 contacts, then will a tertiary contact section show up automatically? 
</li> <li> Add Instant Messenger contact information to people registrations. 
</li></ul> 
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Long_term_Timeframe"></a> Long term Timeframe </span></h2> <ul>
<li> Secure Web Pages access based on Security Contacts listing 
</li></ul> 
<p />
<hr />
<hr />
<p />
<strong><br /></strong>
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Done_please_include_timestamp"></a> Done (please include timestamp) </span></h2>
<p /> <ul>
<li> Admin - edit resource gives me a 404 -- it's looking for resource.php.php -- should be an easy fix? - 2008-5-23-12:3O 
</li> <li> Edit/Display Resource/VO/SC pages need to show current active/inactive status .. and resoruce page should also show Status (ie up/ down maint, etc.) - 2008-5-23-16:50 
</li> <li> Edit_Resource -- we should not allow an admin to choose a random site while editing a resource; they should only be able to choose a site within the chosen facility. If they want to change the facility itself, then we (GOC) will have to do it OR we could add functionality to do that too.. - 2008-5-23-16:50 (GOC Admin users do have the ability to select any site. Normal users do not) 
</li> <li> inactive_list.php: lists no one (I guess because I made everyone active for contacts purposes in the DB ) -- there's a really tiny link in that empty page which when I click, says "An email has been sent to: ... " [empty string]. This page should show anyone who does not have a DN irrespective of whether or not they are an active OIM person. - last week, forgot to move it 
</li> <li> edit group contacts: expects first and last name ... should only expect one name ... and removed middle name - June 4, 2008 
</li> <li> Edit person page should allow switching between group user and person user .. at least for GOC staff. There's a CMS Tier1 user right now in both groups. - June 4, 2008 
</li> <li> add toggle for active/inactive for person group - June 4, 2008 
</li> <li> Add SC information to Resource stuff on Admin interface. Also should be for resource page, I think. - June 4, 2008 
</li> <li> We need to be able to remove contacts, and not just change... (of course there will be ramifications.. for example a resource will become inactive if its primary required contacts is removed.)(we will use an oim-deleter user sometime here, but for now oim-updater) - June 5, 2008 
</li> <li> Added all of Arvind's mail messages and notification messages sent in the pdf - June 5, 2008 
</li> <li> Add/Edit_Resource: We're allowing selection of any resource as parent ... you should only allow resources in a particular site (chosen) as parent resource -- important validation we'll need RSN if not today. June 6,2008 
</li> <li> Add or display time registration was originally submitted, as well as last updated date/time.- Done July 8, 2008 
</li> <li> Scheduled Maintenance Summary Page - Done AG July 4 2008. 
</li> <li> Fix error (again) that makes the same person selectable for primary and secondary contacts.Done (Will be totally revamped when new contact system is created) 
</li> <li> Make "add a new person/group" have same constraits as person (no duplicate email address) Done - KG July 11 2008 
</li> <li> Finish validation of Person Name and Resource Name, etc. --- Did this...and SC and VO. Since SC and VOwill likely never change names, I also locked out changes from regular users to VO/SC names after registering, as was talked about a while back. 
</li> <li> Update GOC Notification to Use OIM contact information -- agopu 2008-07-11 (script on funafuti modified, will go into production on Monday) 
</li> <li> Bug in maintenance submission form: Abhishek somehoe managed to submit maintenance records that had 0000:00:00 00:00:00 as the end_time; so we need to have: one validation (and possibly more) that ensures the end_time cannot be &lt; start time. -kyle fixed this, agopu 2008-07-11 
</li> <li> Medium: Checkboxes to select resource types -- this is done, albeit code handles services for each resource, instead of resource type -agopu 2008-07-11 
</li> <li> Medium: Web Form to send email to goc@ -- done by kyle, agopu 2008-07-11 
</li> <li> Public views of OIM dat  <ul>
<li> VO - done for osg-includes -agopu 2008-07-11 
</li> <li> SC - partially done-agopu 2008-07-11 
</li></ul> 
</li> <li> Finish Quick Links section on OIM home page -- to include view/edit and maintenance links (where applicable) for resources, VOs, SCs, added contacts. Arvind has put together a prototype for this on the dev server. Consider creating pop-up page if number of resources &gt; N. Use icons/images for view/edit/maintenance links. - Done July14 KG 
</li> <li> Disable button in the admin resource list- Done KG July 16 
</li> <li> Clear up confusion re: SE read/write/regex fields or remove them temporarily.<strong>-- THESE HAVE BEEN REMOVED TEMPORARILY - KG July 17<br /></strong> 
</li> <li> Allow Multiple (Currently limited to two) Contacts for Operations and Security Contacts. (July 25th Deadline) -- done by KG -agopu 2008-07-25 
</li> <li> Public, Restricted, and Private access to registration information view. (July 25th Deadline) -- done -agopu 2008-07-25  <ul>
<li> Resource, maintenance info 
</li> <li> SC -- including osg-includes view 
</li> <li> VO -- including osg-includes view 
</li> <li> Facility, site 
</li> <li> person (for GOC view only) 
</li></ul> 
</li></ul> 
<p /> <ul>
<li> Registration Core Infrastructure Service. (July 25th Deadline): This should come with some grouping of resource types.Done 12-aug KG 
</li> <li> Grid Services -- Child elements: {Compute Element, Storage Element {SRM v1, SRM v2, Bestman/Xrootd, GridFTP} } Done 12-aug KG 
</li> <li> Core Infrastructure Service: For example: {Auth/Auth: {VOMS server, GUMS server}, Accounting: {Gratia}, Monitoring: {RSV Collector, BDII Collector} } Done 12-aug KG 
</li> <li> Views for OSG Staff - Done KG Aug 22 
</li> <li> <strong>View 1</strong> List of all active persons and groups sorted by last name, with contact information. - Done KG Aug 22 
</li> <li> <strong>View 2</strong> List of Resources sorted by name, with Primary and Secondary Operations and Security Email - Done KG Aug 22 
</li> <li> <strong>View 3</strong> Same as 2 above but with SC - Done KG Aug 22 
</li> <li> <strong>View 4</strong> Same as 2 above but with VO - Done KG Aug 22 
</li></ul> 
<p />
-- <a href="/bin/view/Main/ArvindGopu" class="twikiLink">ArvindGopu</a> - 11 Jul 2008</div><!-- /patternTopic-->
